description: The investment by Alphabet’s Google is the latest in a string of multibillion-dollar plans by Western tech giants to meet growing computing needs in Southeast Asia.
title: Google Plans $2 Billion for Malaysia Data Center, Cloud Services

description: Google has committed $2 billion in investments in Malaysia, including building its first data center, a new Google Cloud region and further developing artificial intelligence.
title: Google to Invest $2 Billion in Malaysia for AI, First Data Center

description: Southeast Asian ride-hailing and delivery specialist Grab will collaborate with OpenAI to tap generative artificial intelligence to enhance users’ experience.
title: Grab to Collaborate with OpenAI to Enhance User Experience
